body:
How may we help - what is your question?
I can only find the internal signals the first inst of the hier_block module that has been inst multi times.
verilog code:
```
module detal_code(
    input clk,
    input reset
);
endmodule

module sub_top(
    input clk,
    input reset
);
    detail_code u0(
          .clk(clk),
          .reset(reset)
    );
    detail_code u1(
          .clk(clk),
          .reset(reset)
    );
    detail_code u2(
          .clk(clk),
          .reset(reset)
    );
    detail_code u3(
          .clk(clk),
          .reset(reset)
    );
    detail_code u4(
          .clk(clk),
          .reset(reset)
    );
    detail_code u5(
          .clk(clk),
          .reset(reset)
    );
    detail_code u6(
          .clk(clk),
          .reset(reset)
    );
    detail_code u7(
          .clk(clk),
          .reset(reset)
    );
endmodule

module top(
    input clk,
    input reset
);
    sub_top u0_sub_top(
          .clk(clk),
          .reset(reset)
    );
    sub_top u1_sub_top(
          .clk(clk),
          .reset(reset)
    );
endmodule

```

configure file hier.vlt:
```
`verilator config
hier_block -module "detail_code"
hier_block -module "sub_top"

```
trace code:
```
contextp->traceEverOn(true);
ftp = new VerilatedVcdC;
top->trace(tfp, 99);
tfp->open(“dump.vcd”);
```

cmd
```
verilator --hierarchical --trace  -j -cc -CFLAGS  --top-module top top.sv hier.vlt --exe main.cpp --build
```
I can trace (from VCD) 
```
TOP.top.u0_sub_top.u0.u0 details

but,
missing: TOP.top.u0_sub_top.u1 ~ u7 internal signals
missing: TOP.top.u1_sub_top.u0 ~ u7 internal signals

```
Is it a mistake I made, or does the tool not support this kind of trace?
